summary: In this context, 1,2,4-trimethylbenzene is categorized as one of the aromatic hydrocarbons included in the assessment of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) in dwellings. The study groups various VOCs by type, indicating that 1,2,4-trimethylbenzene is part of the broader category of aromatic hydrocarbons, which also includes other compounds like benzene and toluene. However, the specific interactions or implications of 1,2,4-trimethylbenzene within the context of health outcomes are not detailed.
